{"word":"στρατιώτης","slug":"στρατιώτης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>στρατιώτης, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<el>στρατός</el> ‘army’] <b>soldier<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> in central military sense <b><a href='B:470 8:9'>Mt 8:9</a>; <a href='B:470 28:12'>28:12</a>; <a href='B:480 15:16'>Mk 15:16</a>; <a href='B:490 7:8'>Lk 7:8</a>; <a href='B:500 19:2'>J 19:2</a>; <a href='B:510 10:7'>Ac 10:7</a>; <a href='B:510 12:6'>12:6</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ ext.\">ext.</a> sense of one in service to Christ Jesus viewed as a general and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> focus on allegiance to him <b><a href='B:620 2:3'>2 Ti 2:3</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:στρατιά\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:στρατολογέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}